Title: Registered Reports: A Method to Increase the Credibility of Published Reports
Description: From abstract: Ignoring replications and negative results is bad for science. This special issue presents a novel publishing format – Registered Reports – as a partial solution.
Contributors: Brian A. Nosek, Daniel Lakens
Tags: peer review, replication, preregistration, open science

Registered Reports: A Method to Increase the Credibility of Published Reports
From abstract: Ignoring replications and negative results is bad for science. This special issue presents a novel publishing format – Registered Reports – as a partial solution.
